{"text": "I’m not sure you should try and directly compare this to the original, i think that’s a bit unfair. You see where they have taken the old xcom ideas and touched it up with new ideas and features that do work well. No more 5 our terror missions was a nice relief. No base attacks either but i think i can accept that. Overall its a very nice re-imagining/reboot whatever you want to call it that you should not compare directly with the original. Accept it for what it is, and that is a new take on the XCOM I.P sourcing from how it used to be and updated and tweaked to suit the modern audience. Blows away all the other Xcom style games, that have come out over the past 8 years. Id recommend any veteran player of Xcom to go straight to classic mode, the true difficulty of the game, as normal is really for new players of the game. Any veteran will not find much real challenge in doing it on normal, except to see the game through in under 20 hours and get a take how things now work.", "appid": "200510", "steamid": "profiles/76561197963698584", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1350043200.0}
