{"text": "Despite some rough edges, the game is still pure Codemasters racing goodness. It’s a focused game, but it largely hits on the goals it sets out to do, and is better than the first one. Still not as good as Dirt 2 though. All in all, GRID 2 in a very competent addition to the racing genre, with some stunning visuals, varied gameplay, and a fun multiplayer aspect that will keep you coming back for more. The game does suffer slightly by trying cater to everyone rather than sticking to all-out simulation or arcade, but if the more casual racers can persevere through the steep learning curve, there’s enough gameplay here for it to warrant a purchase.", "appid": "44350", "steamid": "profiles/76561198365804041", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "22", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1554120000.0}
