{"text": "Bitmemiş bir oyun olduğunu bilerek aldım ancak bu kadar bitmemiş olduğunu düşünmemiştim.Optimizasyon sorunun bir kenara koyarsak oyun içeriği diye bir şey neredeyse yok. Bütün kaleler, şehirler ve şehrin içerisindeki hanlar birbiriyle benzer ve uzun süredir yeni bir patch yayınlamadılar. Alacak olanlar için, büyük ihtimalle şu haliyle 30 saat oynanıştan sonra sıkılıp aylarca girmeyeceksiniz.Full sürüme çıkmasını bekleyebilirsiniz.", "appid": "261550", "steamid": "profiles/76561198202030350", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1585742400.0}
{"text": "This review will be lengthy in negative details. Please forgive my brashness, but it is honest and people need to know the truth of the state of the game. The TLDR is at the very bottom, but you'll miss valuable information. Yes my title was harsh, but so was this game. The character movement was clunky, the graphics on ultra are still poor and the layout / UI was very awkward to say the least. I will continue to explain why I do NOT recommend this game. Please be forewarned that my opinions on this game are \"harsh\" but honest, as a reviewer of games I will not lie but give truth and share my experience wholly for other consumers. There are many problems with this game. This biggest one is the \"crafting system\" / \"gathering system\". The primary method of finding certain parts / items is to get things from \"loot boxes\" / chests you find all over the ground. The pathetic part of this is that you also need lockpicks for certain chests. Well that's reasonable right? Well in order to craft a lot of things you need a BCU \"Base Command Unit\". Well that's all well and good, but when you spend literal hours / tons of time starting off to find the parts just to make a BCU for your base that's a big issue. That's a very big unacceptable issue to say the least. Then once you get one made you have to farm MORE materials to be able to make X Y Z just to do some \"basic looting\". Another big issue is the AI / animals. You start with 80 or so health and you have a pistol and some ammo. Oh that's good right? Well not really. Your pistol is about as useful as a Fisher Price water pistol. You can put a bullet into a wolf's head at point blank range and it tickles them. The wolf bites you though and you're basically dead. You're torn to shreds, bleeding out and left for dead. You basically use your pistol and what few shots you have to find chickens, kill chickens, get feathers, use feathers to make arrows and then save arrows for hunting more chickens and bunny wabbits UwU for the meatsy weatsy. I know most fans of this game will say \"git gud\" or \"l2p\". Well sure say that as you like, but a survival game shouldn't be a \"tedious\" system of \"follow steps 1 2 3\" and then \"grind a b c\" just to make basic equipment or start a base. If I want to play a walking simulator to find \"loot boxes\" or whatever I could play Death Stranding. The graphics would be much better and far less visually disturbing to say the least. There are many other issues that rise over the time playing this game, but to say the least it doesn't get any better. You're better off taking your money and setting it on fire. You'll at least get some warmth and could probably cook a small piece of food over it or melt a marshmallow at the very least. You could wipe your butt with it and get better use out of it honestly. If you hope to get \"enjoyment\" out of this game if you've played other survival games like Ark, 7 Days, Atlas and such you'll be HIGHLY disappointed to say the least. I might come back to this game, or play some more, and try to \"git gud\" but when a wolf sneezes on me and blows my corpse across the map but a bullet to their head does nothing, that's a big problem.  When you can't put a fishing trap down in water unless you go into water up to your neck that's an issue too (realistically most fish traps are near banks in streams, rivers and lakes as bigger fish hunt minnows, frogs and bugs. Yes I know -Is OnLy GaEm- but it makes no sense that I have to put a fishing trap so far down I have to practically swim down to place it). When I can't make a fire starter without finding \"fuel\" from a box that I have to spend X hours to \"find\" in THE MIDDLE OF THE WOODS JUST TO SURVIVE...it's time to reevaluate your ideas and thoughts of \"balance\". This game is more like a walking simulator than it is a survival game. It's more like a \"find the loot box\" hunting treasure game than it is a survival game. It's more like a beat your head against the wall and have fun simulator than it is a survival game. If you value your money and want to invest it, then my honest opinion and suggestion, find another game with more promise and potential. As it stands right now this is far below par based on most other survival games. Oh by the way did I mention that you can only get fiber from tiny sapling looking trees but there are tons of plants, bushes and cat tail plants everywhere you can't harvest or get anything of value from? Why bother with foliage if you can't even use it? Also you can't \"chop down trees\" or \"gather sticks\". You chop trees until a red X appears showing you can't get anymore wood from a tree then makes sticks from tree trunk logs. You get berries from \"loot boxes\" but can't get them off of the many bushes thrown around everywhere that have NO LITERAL USE (unless it's a fiber bush or medicine plant that looks like a tiny twig with dark green ivy leaves on it). This game, in my honest and truthful opinion, is absolute utter filth and the direction it is going needs to be reevaluated if it wants to ever succeed as a good survival game. Yes it sounds harsh, but this game was far from fun and I've played many EA / Beta / Alpha games. Could this game succeed? Yes, absolutely it could succeed. Will it truly succeed and thrive as it is right now? Maybe, if everyone enjoys walking simulators to find loot boxes and unlock them to scream because they didn't get the 1 item they needed for the 10th time to be able to build a base starting unit. Nothing personal devs. I just didn't like your game. As I said before I will not lie to others. Spend hours walking all over to find \"loot boxes\" to get items you need to make \"basic things\" like fuel to make a \"survival fire starter\" in the middle of NOWHERE. Shoot animals in the head with guns to have them laugh and one shot bite you as you fall over and die. Spend hours looking back on your life wondering why you didn't just set your money on fire instead. Shiver in the cold freezing to death wondering why that 15th loot box didn't have fuel to start a fire and why your pistol can't kill a wolf even if you're shooting it in the head just to starve to death with tons of plant life around you that could have had berries in them. Wonder the meaning of life as you realize that your only hope is at the mercy of RNG loot boxes that are mysteriously popping up all over a survival landscape and you can't craft a single bow drill to start a fire to warm your freezing toes off or cook a chicken that it took 2 bullets to kill from a pistol that looks like a 9MM. Stay. Far. Away. From. This. Game. Until. It. Is. Re-worked. That is my honest, truthful and humble opinion. Take what you will from someone who's put thousands of hours into games and 80%+ have been survival games. Thanks for your time and have a wonderful day. PS: Devs as I stated before it's nothing personal, but the game was just absolutely awful to me.", "appid": "418030", "steamid": "profiles/76561198216594040", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1603713600.0}
