{"text": "I beat this game 100% Motifero Motus is a game where you drive a car down an endless, straight highway. The only buttons required are the up and down arrow keys which you use to shift between the three lanes in order to avoid other vehicles and collect items on the road. There is only one mode and 9 levels, each lasting a minute or two. There is no reason to buy this game, there is no reason to play this game. You start out in an regular car driving down the highway. A randomly generated series of vehicles comes down and you need to avoid them. A bar at the bottom shows you how much further until the stage is finished. There is also money and every once and a while one of two powerups on the track. Each dollar sign you pick up adds 1 point to your total score. Red crosses give you another life. And the fire gives you progress on an 'upgrade' meter.  Collecting these items is really easy and in the case of the money not even worth the effort. The other cars on the road are static and move from the right of the screen to the left at the same speed. The other powerups are nearly pointless. Health adds another life, represented by an image of the starting car, to the top left corner. The symbols will not go past 4 though so every life past 4 will not be visible to the player. The fire builds up a yellow meter that when full changes the appearance of your car. You can do this twice. This has no bearing on gameplay as far as I could tell as I tried the last level with the level 1 and max level cars and experienced no change.  Each time you complete a level you are instantly brought into the next. The only difference between levels is that the speed is increased very slightly and starting at level three cops are added in. The cop cars appear at random and randomly shift lanes. If they hit you you lose 1 life like any other vehicle but because they have no discernible pattern and you have no options but moving up and down it is pure chance if they hit you or not. Even with that issue there's next to no penalty for losing all your lives. You keep all whatever score and car level you had when you lost and just have to start the most recent level from the start. And unless you are trying to get every single dollar on the road its actually  difficult to lose all your lives in a level. WHen you finish level nine you are told your final score and then dropped back on the main screen. Out of curiosity I played the last level again and still had the same car and score from when I won and beat it again leaving me with a higher score. So even the high score is a sham because theres nothing stopping you from just playing that level forever to get the highest score ever! But why would you bother? This entire game screams mediocrity. I wouldnt be suprised if it was actually a school project as it has all the things a beginners course in game design would teach you. The art is plain with the road just having random white spots to serve as 'detail'. There is next to no animation save for a single frame where the car turns slightly when switching lanes and a blinking fire effect when upgrading. The music is a single annoying track that can be turned off thankfully. The sound effects are exactly what you would expect. It even freeezes on occasion to load the next random set of cars.", "appid": "581470", "steamid": "profiles/76561198041006664", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1487764800.0}
