{"text": "Recent review is going based on most recent updates: Im reviewing/updating using game update #24 and providing an important forum post below. Please check links provided in review below for verifications. This game turned into a group farm of friends that slowly expanded into what it is today. We started with 3-4 people farming on the same farm and having a blast. The game did not seem all that grindy but just enough to still make it enjoyable. The only thing we noticed was the medals were coming in slowly but steady. Also that the farm space was very limited and lacking achievements since we were all achievement hunters we wanted something especially late game to keep us going longer.  Along the way, we made friends and met other people who needed a push out of the early game. We also love teaching and helping others so like any other game and platform we fell into our usual roles of building a small community of farmers in this game. Now that is some of the background information as to why I, personally, got a lot to say on this subject.  When boost meters were introduced, we are running into more greedy and rude people who simply come into your farm to take and don't do anything else not even plow. Now the developers are giving crops that take longer a better boost and harvesting a buff. How does this affect farms and social activity in-game?  We already have a problem and you are adding to it. This would mean anyone trying to level would need to close their farms since the balancing is now more broken than ever. Greedy harvesting will only get worse for the owner. Now we must idle the game more and more and hurt the active players who want to get the same enjoyment and rewards but it gets worse.  How does this affect new players? Significantly slower leveling. Take the melons example, which was the next thing to plant beside lettuce early game. Try restarting to a new farm, and see how much slower progress will be and how many of you will leave farms open now with this new update. Higher level farmers idle more for the $$ then actually staying and helping and talking to newer players. This update not only does it promote such behavior but rewards it to an extent. I can focus on my farm only and care about how much I am still making which might be a lot less but I do not feel the struggle since I am only capitalizing on the work of lower levels for my own self-gain while they only seem to either harvest for XP or boost meter. I can think like other self-centered people and not think of how this affects new people and their experience. I got something to compare it to, and have restarted more than a few times not just by building a new farm but starting over with other new people coming into the game. Newer players are ignorant of how bad this game is turning into. I do not mind changes, or even nerfs where its needed since they are of course, necessary at some points but what I'm against is mindless nerfs, broken nerfs where in this game more than once the developer has had to go back and be pointed out to correct yet another brainless nerfs.  You are nerfing short-term items into the ground and focus on crops that take longer for the sole purpose of limiting interactions? What if I do not want to idle the game but play it actively and still profit as much? Why are your nerfs focused on hurting active players who want to still enjoy the game and focused on idle farming in this game. Why not have it balanced for both types of gameplay? Why not build the game into both a fun relaxing game and a grind fest? You cant say viable options have not been posted. I have seen a few around but you are set on nerfs that only hurt your game more. A prestige system would help keep players who actually want to grind out your game happy and those that don't can simply keep working on farming. Changing crop color into gold once it reaches level 100. Intro new items without a hard nerf to see how it does. Making newer crops just as good if not better so we may mix things up. Providing the necessary info for us to compare it to. Build on the game instead of going back and nerfing and destroying decent items like sprinklers (thank you for changing back) that are balancing the game enough that player progress is steady.  Now, what has this done to our small community of players and friends? At least from our end, we might open the game a few times but I'm seeing more people dropping the game. We have moved on to other games but I want us to come back to this game but with each hard nerf it is making it harder to stand behind this developer and this game.  I already see my own small farmer's community leaving this game behind and moving into other games. I myself have been holding on to this game for what it used to be and NOT what it is becoming, and like in other games developers is the one hurting the game more than anything else.  The main group eventually split up to get some of the achievements we needed. Mind you that the achievements were also something that needed to be changed and voiced on forums/discord. It was changed to allow everyone who has full rights to also be granted the achievement as the ower. Enjoy! Now we are faced with mindless nerf after nerf because I do not know why this dev is set on nerfing anything you interact with a lot. I feel as if in upcoming nerf wave we will see one even on asphalt.... *sigh*  Lastly, where did the dev give details of nerfs on fish, trees, crops, and animals? Gave us numbers and a general reason as to why these big nerfs are happening. Nowhere are details or info given.  At the end of the day, it is your game and if this is the direction you want to continue taking the game one of the few things I can do is no longer support the game but advice against future purchases based on my current experiences with the game. I at least attempted to once again make a change before considering quitting your game again. My only hope is you consider some of the reports given to you by active players who actually worked hard to build a community within your game and have provided more than just opinions but numbers to support them. Also, do consider listening to the people who actually contributed to the game selflessly helping and providing active feedback on your game on both forums and discord. I just want to add that at the end of the day I can choose not to care about all the nerf drama and focus on my own self-gain and have not taken the time to give feedback on any thread. Since I did play the game when it was actually (better) I got my moneys worth..  ======= My first review of the game when it was not this bad of a standing. Posted: Mar 21 @ 5:13pm\t Updated: Apr 24 @ 8:24am ======= Update #24 - Sheep & New Fences! MAY 31\t- WAAGHMAN ======= I am working hard to continue to provide feedback and hopes of further changes to improve gameplay for both idle and active players.  Here is a link to some of this feedback and gameplay ideas. ======= Devs dishonesty via omission of updates.", "appid": "673950", "steamid": "profiles/76561198079748456", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "28", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1521633600.0}
