{"text": "This review will be updates when I play more. I know these is a teaser and I really like the whole idea to make a remake. However, I think that it goes wrong direction. And here's why: 1) Dialogue system. It is the biggest problem right now. Please, don't do the modern wheel of answers. It is bad because of two things: it's too simple to play the role and it it too complex to get the information fast. Clarifying #1: dialogue wheel is a really bad idea for Gothic, which always had complex dialogue system, which allowed to get all necessary information and at the same time fully control the answers of the character, which allowed to play the role. Clarifying #2: system was technically more simple. All those new character animations, long pauses between the phrases, inability to skip the phrase when you read fast just artificially makes the dialogue longer. 2) World feels too lifeless and it seems to be lacking freedom. I could not speak with Diego after the first talk and taking the first quest. In the intro there were to little interactive objects. I could not jump from the bridge into waterfall. 3) Character changes. He speaks way too much. This is veeery annoying, Almost as much annoying as long, unskippable and too fancy dialogue system. Also too many cutscenes. 4) Color paletter is to bright and colorful. 5) Some issues with lore. Prisoners did not control the whole Khorinis, like entry video says. Character was not punched in the face in the beginning :D What I liked: 1) New combat system. It requires polishing as it now feels way less dynamic than the original one because of the missing combos. 2) Presence if consequences system.", "appid": "950670", "steamid": "profiles/76561198016197831", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1576324800.0}
{"text": "I see why people like it. But this game has too many issues for me to recommend it. The gameplay seems to keep shifting to cater to more casual players. 70% of the time you will never see where you are getting shot from. Yea that's realistic, but not fun. This game badly needs the \"eye squint\" feature from Arma in order to zoom in on the landscape. Even a 15% zoom would help a lot. Also the emphasis on vehicles is a turn off. It's a lot less tactical when you can just send in a BTR (and aircraft/helis in the future) to capture points. The team with the most vehicles left will almost always win. Bottom line. Realistic? Yea. Fun? Not really.", "appid": "393380", "steamid": "profiles/76561197990876886", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1565956800.0}
