{"text": "An interesting little game *BUT* Like other Kickstarter projects, this little title has made it's way to Steam. Gameplay-wise, it's very simplistic. As the main character, you are set in charge as the alpha decision maker for a group of plane crash survivors. You do this by being presented with a simplistic cost/consequence decision tree that makes it apparent very quickly that no matter your choices, not everyone is going to survive. However, despite it's indie-artistic charm, that's about where the appeal ends. On my first playthrough, I finished the game in about 30 minutes; taking the time to read each dialogue. My following seassion was pounded out in less than 15 as I found myself skipping through the dialogue simply due to lack of interest and the non-existant story. Your fellow survivors all speak in this mumble language (much like in the Sims) which also became an irritant. If there had been actual voice acting, perhaps that would have been enough to encourage one to listen to the dialogue. Normally titles like this on Steam I would expect to see in the range of $5 to $10. But at $16.99 CDN there is just simply nothing new or interesting enough here to warrant such a high price. Thankfully I picked this title up during a sale at 80% off, otherwise I would have been looking into the refund process.", "appid": "234920", "steamid": "profiles/76561197970522234", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1450094400.0}
