{"text": "Incredibly obtuse and unintuitive interface that ranges from difficult to impossible to actually configure and manage from within VR--and I say this as a veteran of 20+ years of IT work. I'm reasonably comfortable either figuring things out for myself or searching for solutions, but trying to do something basic like pinning a Twitch chat window where I wanted it was an exercise in frustration. Put simply, if you are: * Comfortable with doing a bunch of your own research * Investing a possibly-extended amount of time into configuration and tweaking * Don't mind doing most of your that setup work from outside VR, then going back into VR to check your work * Have something unusual you want to do that isn't covered by other overlay apps Then it's possible that this app might have some flexibility that others lack. I couldn't tell you--the initial experience of trying to use it was so aggravating that I didn't get that far. I just gave up and refunded it. If we didn't have any other options, I probably would've reached out to the dev and tried harder--but we do. If all you want to do is pin windows in the world in an intuitive, drag-and drop way using the VR environment itself, I'd recommend OVR Toolkit instead. It has its own quirks, but the workflow needed to accomplish the kinds of basic tasks typical to most VR users is much more straightforward, and probably won't require as much Googling for tutorials.", "appid": "586210", "steamid": "profiles/76561197970332903", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1596196800.0}
