{"text": "Before I get hate for my low amount of hours, I will have you know I did have a Founders account that is unrecoverable according to support (insert their frownie face here). After years, decided to try the game again and I just got recently banned using a function they developed and actively want you to use (insert unresponsive [DE]Chris here).  Gameplay: 9 Graphics: 9 Community: 4 Cosmetics: 10 Updates: 8 PVE: 9 PVP: 4 Support: 1 : The gameplay itself to me seems to be relatively unique. Can play with a controller, or with your keyboard. Personally, I prefer the keyboard. Rest your palm on the ctrl, and thumb on space and you're golden. Controller, only used it once, but the PC version reeaallly isn't meant to be played with a controller. Feel wise, it's just... off. Maps, can be quite repetitive to the point where you can remember every tile set, but not as repetitive as Diablo 3's tile sets. Weapons seem to be actually accurate based on the tooltips. Some games tend to mess that up, even the major games out there. The UI is kinda... bleh... if you're a new player. Takes a lot of getting used to. Overall all, gotta say it's really smooth, with only very minor problems that would annoy someone.  : Not much to say about this. The graphics speak for themselves. Even on the lowest settings they seem to still be pretty amazing. Sometimes the game is kinda slow at loading it so it looks like a slab of paint then it corrects itself. Doesn't matter if I am using a Top-end PC or just a general cheap gaming system, it does the same thing. Besides that it's amazing.  : The community is... like if 4chan had a baby with hormonal college kids and created a 7 year old version of those 2 combined. You'll occasionally find someone that's not messing with you and actually wants to help or play. If you love Bowsette conversations, this is the best chat for you. If you like Pineapple on your pizza, make sure to let everyone know that. People will whine if you do nothing in a match, though it's kinda hard to sometimes especially if they map kill. People will leave if you go to fast despite it being a fast pace game. People don't go much past wave 10-15 in defense modes because all they want to do is farm instead of chill and play. Overall, community is terrible for the quality of the game you're getting.  : Cosmetics in this game are quite top-notch compared to what you usually get in games. This one, they even have a tool where you can submit cosmetics and even get paid for them if it's accepted. You get 30% in it's sales which isn't to bad. The quality of the cosmetics, even non-professional ones submitted by players with the restrictions given to them, are still amazing. : From the ones I have actually been there for it seems to have good quality in them. However, like all games, they tend to not fix some old stuff, and wait about 78 patches till they remember again. Like filler text in some tooltips when selecting a planet or item. Which in turn leads bad lore from the lore fanbois.  : Not to much to get into on this one. PvP is basically non-existent and not worth doing if I am going to be honest. PvE is what the game is purely focused on. Lots of different types of modes. Maps still sit on a few varied tile sets, and you can have Space Battle Maps, Underwater Battles, and just plain pew pewing on normal modes.  : The reason I rated this so low is because the support is one of the worse I have seen. And I have had a lot of bad experiences with support. At the lowest I would usually rate is a 3-5, but this company is complete ass when it comes to support. First off, when the game was first released I bought a Founders. Not the cheap one either. I went for the Grand Master pack. The email I used at the time was yahoo. And that's when yahoo had a huge chunk of hacks and didn't say anything about it. Well, lost access to that account. Yahoo wouldn't help (of course), so came to DE support to get an email change. Well, I need access to my email to change it... even supplied every single purchase I ever made with them. Nothing. Not good enough to help save my account, can't even change a stupid email. Now, coming back years later at the request of my friend. I started getting a need for platinum. My friend would often send me things like plat, or frames, or prime sets he had extras of. Well, I started to use warframe.market that trading website, even the riven one. Apparently, one of the people I traded is a known platinum seller. So instead of just banning the guy selling platinum, DE chooses to ban every that remotely trades with these people. I sent maaannnyy pictures of not just my emails, but my paypal and bank showing I legit don't own a card, nor can I buy anything online. Absolutely no response from the lovely [DE]Chris. You got one job man, do it. My dad is IT and runs multiple servers, trains people, AND does support, but still manages to actually support. He's on a 2 man team right now for a major company. You guys have what, 200-500 employees and can't have a proper support system? Come on. You see this is an issue. You've seen it for years, but unfortunately, your support gets a 1/10 for being so bad.", "appid": "230410", "steamid": "profiles/76561198079889111", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1538827200.0}
