{"text": "I had some hopes when trying this game out, I shouldn't have.  I don't know what is worst about the game, but I'll just point out some facts: - Specs are pretty high, had to turn some graphic options down on my notebook (i5 with Nvidia 3100 1 Gb and 8 Gb DDR3) to run 100% smooth. I expected good graphics when I saw that, I was wrong - Graphics look like a 90's game, some light effects and shadows that seem to be more modern, but it still sucks. - Gameplay seemed promising from the description but it's just awefull. Racing sucks, car control is bad, turning just makes you lose speed, which is low anyways, you can't hit or do anything to your opponent, you will always race in straight lines, car upgrades have sick prices and you get close to no upgrade. you have to bet your money on races on straight lines and you will lose to opponents with weaker cars if you don't upgrade enough. There is no fun in the gameplay, that's the worst part. Play it only if you want to see some low riders cars and if yo uare bored to look at google images (which have a lot better graphics btw). One of the worst games I ever played", "appid": "65070", "steamid": "profiles/76561198050370092", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1414497600.0}
{"text": "Its been a while since i did a negative review to a game but this game has recieved the cake.. Single player is amazing but the online has so much problems that i always find and encounter.... Online Problems: 1.Infinite time for loading screens that not load properly. 2.Cheaters/Modders basically in every big session you find. 3.Bad Servers 4.Too many bug/glitches that can be found in some certain heists and missions. 5.too much chinese people that take over the game and speak the square language. 6.Since 14/09/20: i cant even join to my friends anymore.... this game is absolutely terrible (DONT PLAY ONLINE). Rockstar are making good games i cant argue with that but they are bad at taking control in their Online Service so much...  I played this game for so long to experience these problems and more about and enough this is too much for me to handle.... and seriously this game is 7 or more years old and still these issues exists... The Only way to play this Online Garbage Service properly is to create a solo session by yourself and grind for money or play with your friends which for me its impossible....  This game by far is the game with the worst Online Service i ever encounterd.... Rockstar please do me a favor and fix these issues and make this game better again please.... i guess from now on i'll stick to story mode until the time that rockstar will finally take advantage and fix their game!!!. if you dont want to experience the problems i encountered...stick to story mode and thats it it'll make your brain feel much better trust me... Single Player rate:10/10 Online rate:1/10", "appid": "271590", "steamid": "profiles/76561198039456691", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1476187200.0}
{"text": "No. Just no. They tried to create a mix of Nausicaä, Evangelion without mechas and Princess Maker, however something went terribly wrong. While the general world building and story premise are quite intriguing, it soon becomes drowned in poorly done slice-of-life storyline. Most of your choices don’t matter that much, and your daughter doesn’t have various personality types, like, for example, in Princess Maker or Ayanami Rising Project. It’s the same air-headed and overly optimistic Ciel every time. The only thing you can more or less change are the main storyline ending and Ciel’s career choice shown in an epilogue. All 3 variants of the main story ending can be easily achieved via save scamming during the end of the game because only end-game choices matter in that case. As for career choices – they’re mostly affected by stats, and the game designed the way that once you unlock one ending, you’re given access to the ending list where all criteria for each career path are indicated. Now with the cast of characters. While they’re interested at first, soon you realize they’re all too anime. Like, too much. And no, I’m not talking about art style – their personalities, speech and actions are too anime cliché. Once you realize and crack the formula of their behavior, these characters have quickly become robbed of their personality – there’s not much of them except following the same cliché behavior and speech patterns. Plus more you play, more you realize that the whole grim dystopian setting and story has been written and presented in such childish way that you can’t even take it seriously anymore. The conflict between humanity and nature? Deaths? A first war between humans after, like, a hundred year of peace? Nah, it’s just a background for overly naïve slice-of-life. The developers should’ve decided better on which category of players to aim – to create more mature and realistic story or to make more heroic, naïve and teen-orientated one. It seems they’ve decided to place it somewhere in-between, and now it’s neither fish nor fowl.", "appid": "738270", "steamid": "profiles/76561198144117226", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "47", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1583755200.0}
