{"text": "Hero is overpowered but NOT overly cautious True Ending took me 4 playthru and 9 hours to achieve, without looking at any game guide. Since this game doesn't require any grinding for EXP/gold. Each playthru sees the hero with 999stats and 99999gold. Each playthru lasts 2-3 hours, the True ending is revealed at NG+3 and no other benefits for bringing the game to NG+4.  See my in-game hour and true end screenshot:   I think this game might last 4hrs if I relied on a game guide, instead of saving and loading if there are time wasted doing nothing. Grinding party members doesn't have any benefits except if doing Yona's quest which requires her to be grinded until she unlocks a spell. Even a hero with weakened 800+stats is stronger than your party member. Though Yona is just as good when trained and given the hero's equipment. Game tutorials states Fatigue causes faster stats drain, rest up often. Fights are really shallow, spam Hero ultimate attack, replenish MP by resting/MP curatives and spam again. There isn't a need to even gear up accordingly to be immune to elements since you can just spam healing spells/item while the hero spam his fire spell. If enemy is immune to fire, Hero simply use normal attacks. There are 5 dungeons, each of them took less than 5mins to navigate since there are consumable items that allow you to walk through enemies without initiating battle. There's 1 in each dungeon, Vivi sells you 3x for 1 each, shops also carry it in limited stock, enemy drop them as well.  The town doesn't serve much purpose. Merely to speak to the heroine to accept their quest and buy roses for romance event when staying in the inn. The shops' equipment are nowhere superior than those dropped by enemies. And what's the purpose of a warehouse for storage when items don't carry over to next playthru? Random events aren't random. Exit/ enter from world map/ dungeon's safe room to get certain event to spawn. If quests require you to fight a character 3x, it can all be completed in the same location. So this game is just as linear instead of having NG+ entirely new. The multiple ending is just the funeral scene with the Heroine and NPC with different dialogues/ outcome. Not the one-liner but 3-liners which the player will sit through each time the game is completed. 3-liner for meeting the character, 1 for completing main quest, 1 for completing additional quest. Each Heroine has 2 quest, which require 2 playthru to finish. There's a quest asking for 250k gold, gold given in previous playthru do not carry over. (Another item can be given even if you can't donate 250k gold) The things that carry over are just quest completion. Partial completion do not carry over. Quests are uninspiring too. They range from: Fetch 'item', kill 40 monsters, kill 1 unique monster. On my NG+2, they start becoming repetitive. For choosing wrong choice at True Ending boss fight, you get a 'game-over' and immediately brought to title screen. Seems too difficult for them to have cutscene or dialogue for that? The music in this game isn't Kenji Ito's greatest work unfortunately. This game seems unfinished to me. Alot of mechanics introduced aren't properly implemented for a purpose. Even fishing is just equipping a rod, play the mini-game without any controller inputs and rely on RNG.  Wait for a sale if what I described doesn't deter you.", "appid": "1054050", "steamid": "profiles/76561198180550915", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "17", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1583150400.0}
