{"text": "Such an awesome game in so many ways from suspense,team work,dope guns and equipment and it all works fairly and the game play is smooth and tactical,but in and among all that greatness lays the core issue stopping this game from taking off and that is matchmaking and the ability to train and still have fun at lower levels. Im level 30+ and even though i have a fairly good selection of weaponry and gear the game is just unplayable after level 25+ since once you pass that threshold youre now paired with all the level 100's since there isnt any kinda level wall after 25. it makes no sense its like giving a solider one week of training and sending him to the front. You go from having a fun time under 25 then you start getting your ♥♥♥♥ pushed in. And i do want to go on the record of saying yes ive killed a few 100's and i know you can still stand a chance depending on location/situation but so much of the toe-to-toe fighting in this game relies on your gear choice and current hunters levels.  Simple level bracketing would solve this so quickly i dont care if im playing against 20-30 levels higher then myself i can handle that sometimes but tossing me to people who are 70+ levels ahead over and over just gets boring. The levels 100's fear losing nothing and are tough af so it forces you into a play style whether you like it or not since you'll just get your ♥♥♥♥ pushed in otherwise. When matchmaking is fixed this game will be amazing until then i just dont have much fun playing a one sided game.", "appid": "594650", "steamid": "profiles/76561198019441239", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "78", "votes_funny": "7", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1555675200.0}
{"text": "Ok really wanted to enjoy this but until they do something about the frame rate issues how the hell can i ?????? I meet more than even the recommended specs and at times Claire moves like she should and then she all of a sudden pauses and then runs like a complete mad woman for 3 seconds and then back to normal!!!!!!!! Shortest review i have ever done and i will say that until they patch this and make it playable (as its unplayable in this state) it is one i would not reccomend to anyone and to be honest its one you should avoid FACT!!!!! JUST TO POINT OUT!!!!!!!!!!!!! After playing through the first part and experiencing nothing but framerate issues and stuttering i got to the point in the game where you play as Barry, Now why is it that the game runs really well from here on in but doesnt play well in the first opening chapter???????????? No matter what there must be some issues with the game as it runs well at some points and not at others - this can only mean one thing,the game needs some work and needs patching. (ALSO THE OWNERS OF THE PS4 VERSION ARE REPORTING ISSUES WITH FRAMERATE AND STUTTERING AS WELL SO THE PROBLEM SEEMS TO BE MORE WIDE-SPREAD THAN IT FIRST APPEARED)", "appid": "287290", "steamid": "profiles/76561198082918293", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "139", "votes_funny": "9", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1424865600.0}
{"text": "The DRGW SD50 is a good addition to your own collection. Since it was developed by Digitial Train Model (DTM) it comes with a lot of features that aren't found on many of the other US DLCs created by the developer, Dovetail Games. It has the same awesome sounds as the GP50 that was released by DTM but with a different horn and includes a gyre light on the nose. The paint texture is solid and crisp.  However, it does come with negatives. It has some game breaking bugs in it that make it very difficult to run. You may expierence drops in frame rate if you use some on the interior cab lights. I also would not buy it at full price, you are only getting 1 single locomotive; no rolling stock. The bugs are too game breaking, and the what you pay for and what you get in this DLC don't weigh properly. You get 1 buggy but sounds and looks really good locomotive. I can't give this a recommendation. 6.5/10 *This does inpact my feelings about this DLC but I wish that DTM & DTG would have also developed the standard cab SD60 which looks identical to this model the only difference is the some exterior grills. All they would have to do is reskin this model, and change the sounds, thats it.", "appid": "325955", "steamid": "profiles/76561198041776289", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1536753600.0}
