{"text": "Deus Ex: The Fall is a prequel to Deus Ex: Human Revolution, an amazing game. It has the same setting like HR and does an admirable job at the dystopian cyberpunk the series is known for. Unfortunately this is only a port from iOS and that effects on the gameplay.  You play as Ben Saxon who is trying to find the truth behind the drug conspiracy because they are very rare and all people with augmentations need them. He was betrayed from his employer, a private Military – the tyrants. Now his life and all augmented people are in danger. The story part is nothing much and not really deep.  The gameplay is the same as in Deus Ex: HR, Ben Saxon has the same augments and abilities as Adam Jensen. You need to hack objects like locked door, are able to do takedowns, crawl through vents and shoot form cover. Next to the Main missions you can talk to NPC’s and maybe they give you a side mission and/or explore the world. You upgrade your augmentations and weapons while you playing stealth or kill anyone. As I said, this is a port from a tablet and this is a big problem. On the tablet it’s nice to play this game but the controls on a PC are terrible. They are clunky, unresponsive and the combat from cover is useless. What is very annoying is the fact, that bodies disable after a few seconds and you have many loading times. Just a terrible port. By the way there is an ingame store which allows you to buy ammo and gear every time. That’s unrealistic and too easy. You can shoot all enemies down like Rambo, you only need enough money. For a mobile game its impressive but on the PC it’s not very well, it looks often very ugly. The textures look a bit weak but with the lights and shadows it’s okay. The User Interface is without a Touchscreen just terrible. It’s so annoying and uncomfortable to navigate with mouse and keyboard in Deus Ex: The Fall. The best part of the game is the Soundtrack form Michael McCann which create the amazing Soundtrack for Human Revolution. The voice acting is okay but nothing special. Deus Ex: The Fall on Steam is for fans only. If you like Human Revolution, you can try it but don’t expect a game like this. It's not a bad game but I can't recommend it, it has too much negative points. It’s a game for tablets and not for the PC, note that. If you are a hardcore fan of the franchise, than go for it. If you are not, don’t buy it. No matter what you are, wait for a sale or buy it in a key store. Don’t buy this for the full price, it’s not worth it, also not as a hardcore fan.", "appid": "258180", "steamid": "profiles/76561198042947854", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1466078400.0}
