{"text": "I'm giving this game a thumbs down, but I'm not negative about it.  When I started the game the graphics jumped out at me, it's very colorful. I was very happy with my first impression. It feels like you're in a Disney cartoon. My pet dog was waiting for me and I spotted a bone, stick and ball I could throw. Unfortunately I couldn't reach any of them as the VR ground was lower than my physical floor. So I had to go into my oculus settings and fake a higher physical floor in order to reach stuff in this game... Petting the dog was also a disappointment to me as the dog barely responds to it.  If I compare this to the robot dog in the free game The Lab, that dog was more interactive and felt much more real.  Having pointed all of this out, I hope they will fix the bugs and make the dog much more interactive like make it roll over to rub its belly. I've waited for this kind of thing for many months and for the price of 4 euros I will keep the game and see if my nephew and niece enjoy it as much as the robot dog.", "appid": "1394140", "steamid": "profiles/76561198170802249", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1598875200.0}
