{"text": "I like and dislike this game at the same time. I don't like that you have to repair your ship everytime you make a character and enter into a linear storyline where you have to mine certain things just to stay in the same solar system. I like the crafting and items with the exception of the excess amount of vanity items. Mobs seem to be far more difficult in some cases than they need to be. I do not like being forced to do missions just to get your ship fixed. I do like missions to upgrade your ship, I do not like having to start a mission from the beginning if my character dies.  Multiplayer: UGH!!! The public servers I find on the internet are mostly all RP. Not that I have an issue with RP, I have an issue with the lack of co-op style servers for building your character, and once again, creating a new character puts you into a linear vacuum, all the missions are single player even when playing in multiplayer mode, which may lend to why there are so many RP servers where your character must already be set up. Updates? You mean player developed mods that have been implemented into the game and called an \"update\"?     I absolutely do not like the developers or the admin team in place that moderates the forums. Chucklefish may make great games that people enjoy but I for one will never purchase anything else this group makes until they develop a better rapport with the Steam community. I do not recommend this game and will not recommend it until the linear aspect of it has been minimized and their customer relations improve. So, for now this is my review.", "appid": "211820", "steamid": "profiles/76561197994563234", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1458907200.0}
