{"text": "This game used to be really fun, then the update's kept taking it in the wrong direction. The community spoke up, gave our take on it, voiced our worry. We loved the class system, we loved duo's we loved solo's when they arrived but that last patch... Good lord almighty that last patch...  It tanked everything, removed solo's, duo's made it all a mess, the weapons are far from balanced and now with the removal of what made the game heavily unique this ship is sinking, and it's sinking fast.  Maybe I'll change my review when the game is fixed, it's still of course 'early access' but they keep making changes going in the opposite direction of what the players want.", "appid": "813820", "steamid": "profiles/76561198006979786", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1537963200.0}
{"text": "An sich ein nettes Spiel , halt fast das gleich wie Agar.io. Für zwischendurch recht nett wobei ich nun nach 22 Stunden sagen muss Agar.io. ist besser. Negative Punkte weshlab das Spiel nen Daumen runter bekommt wären da zb. - Das Matchmaking System ist unterirdisch schlecht , man wird in den Clankriegen mit Clans zusammengewürfelt die zum einem vom Level und von der Ausrüstung her schon garnicht passen (zum beispiel man selbst zu 3 mit Level 1-15 und der Gegner zu 5 mit Level 37-50) also so fern man selbst niemanden hat der dort 3-4 stellige Beträge an Echtgeld reinsteckt hat man von der Ausrüßtung (erfahrung ganz zu schweigen) gar keine chance  - Es gibt verschiede Spielmoduse die teilweise gar solo sein sollen (Battel Royal zb. , wobei das hier eher Hungerspiele heißt ^^) man aber dennoch ÜBERALL die Möglichkeit besitzt mit seinen Leuten reinzugehen und dort dann den Server zu übernehmen  - Das Spiel ist kostenlos aber dennoch bereits fertig und dafür noch teilweise recht verbugt , wobei die hälfte von dem was nach einem Fehler ausschaut dann doch nur auf die fantastische Zusammenlegeung der Leute liegt , so wie es manchmal lagt , warscheinlich Leute aus Europa mit Leuten aus Asien zusammengeschmießen , wobei das nicht möglich ist da Server immer Regions begunden sind ^^ aber es kommt halt so rüber :D ( Rechner defenitiv nicht dran schuld da neu und neue Spiele dort auf Ultra flüssig laufen :P) - gibt vielleicht noch paar mehr dinge die mir jetzt gerade mal wieder nicht einfallen , schreibt sie halt dazu aber mir persönlich reicht das aus um dann doch wieder zur Wurzel Agar zurück zu gehen da wie gesagt die Clan Sache eh nicht funzt.", "appid": "389570", "steamid": "profiles/76561198021004053", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1454241600.0}
{"text": "Kilta is a tactical auto battler featuring item management.  You are a Guildmaster and start with two units. To get more, you need to improve your reputation. Doing Quests (mostly hunting enemies right now) will improve it. The more quests you do, the more units want to join your guild. You can choose between two units. In total, you can have 16 as the UI suggests (that many aren't in the game right now) and up to five can go on a quest together (battle).  You start with a few items in your inventory and get new ones after quests. They are two different items. Weapons and clothes. Both give you bonuses (like +5atk and +1speed, etc.). Each unit can have one weapon and one piece of clothes.  There is also a special ability you can use during a battle. There are just four and you can select one each battle (e.g. heal a character one time during a battle). Aside from that, you can choose where your units stand in a battle. There are nine places to chose from. After that, you just wait and watch.  Sadly, there is not much content. I played a bit over one hour and saw everything the game has to offer aside from a few dialog options.  Talking about dialogs. The characters are really charming and the story is good enough. The music is also pretty good and paired with the beautiful artwork, they deliver an atmospheric product which is the strongest aspect of this game.  Now let's talk about the \"tactical\" in tactical auto battler. Sadly, it doesn't feel like there is anything tactical about the battles. Aside from changing to better equipment and units between quests, I didn't do anything and still won (almost) every battle. In my first run, I lost against the boss. After that, I noticed a small question mark in the tavern. That is the so-called \"tutorial\".  All in all, I can't recommend the game in its current state. They need to improve the \"tactical\" part of the game and add content to justify the asking price of around 10€/USD. The characters are the overall atmosphere is lovely and well-made which shows they work hard on it. I'm sure this review will turn into a positive one in a few months (if they push out enough content/updates).", "appid": "1401560", "steamid": "profiles/76561198022412208", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "13", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1606219200.0}
