{"text": "I really wanted to know what's with the overwhelmingly positive reviews, I was really hoping for a crazy story that would make me cry like a little girl. Unfortunately all I got was a slice-of-life visual novel with some really lovable characters and an amazing art style. It really didn't give me my story fix even though it really had its sub-plots set very well that I hoped they would all connect in the end. It's decent, but you might want to use up your time on better experiences.  With my personal rating system I would give it a 5.3/10. (Immersion 10/10, Gameplay 2/10, Story 4/10)", "appid": "447530", "steamid": "profiles/76561198248136782", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1527854400.0}
