{"text": "FaeVerse Alchemy is a puzzle game which could have been extremely addictive weren't it that the game just seems unfair at times (or I just don't get the game).  The game is a bit like Bejeweled, you match 3 or more of the same icons together to score points and try to avoid them from reaching the top. The only difference here is that once you combine 3 (or more) of them together they change into another icon.  In general it's a good game but what ruined it for me were the powerups that keep appearing in the game and you only know what they are doing if you play the game a lot of times. There are some that just take away 1 icon or some that destroys everything vertically or some that destroy everything from the same color, I get that. But then there are also powerups that simply do whatever and add a whole line or do nothing.  Graphics look fine, music is fine aswell but it gets boring listening to only one track the whole time. Basically the randomnous of this game killed it for me to give this one a positive review. Also, it's still in Early Access so since this a game from 2014, it probably will never be finished.", "appid": "282880", "steamid": "profiles/76561197970064749", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1589889600.0}
{"text": "The game upon launching displayed 4 times zoomed in on my 4k monitor, meaning I could not actually use the menu. I had to every time I started the game hold alt and enter in order to force the game into windowed mode which somewhat fixes the issue while in a window. Then when I entered the options menu, the game zoomed in 4 times again making the game unplayable. When I forced the window to shrink, the menu visibly shrunk but reacted as if it was still zoomed in, meaning I could not leave or alter the menu. Due to the default controls being unusable with my touchpad and ps4 controller, I cannot play the game. Upon posting in discussion about this, while I did receive replies, none of them fixed the problem. Thus I must give a thumbs down due to this fundamental technical issue and pursue a refund.", "appid": "742460", "steamid": "profiles/76561198065405576", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1519214400.0}
