{"text": "Going from Berseria to Vesperia, the game feels dated in terms of combat which the series is known for its engaging combat system. Having started the game on hard, at the very first dungeon, options seem limited but based on the basic mechanics of attacking, moving and blocking overall feels clunky. The recovery time of basic attack and arte is so long that the moment normal-arte chain is finished, the enemy will counter-attack and blocking doesn't execute faster to block a counter-attack. There is neither backdash or dodge to counter this. So much as to attack, get hit, attack get hit OR attack, get hit, move away and wait for opening to attack. In fact this way of combat is done so that you block much earlier, instead of blocking when you already know the enemy is going to counter attack after your combo chain.  Overall, this is a very basic combat system which I felt is a lost opportunity for them to implement things from later installment. All they had to do is removed the clunkiness and the game will be enjoyable and comparable to other tales game released after the PS3 era.", "appid": "738540", "steamid": "profiles/76561198180550915", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1593604800.0}
